      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/output-comparison-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison using normalized RMS error and U95 prediction intervals. Hemolysis index prediction error < 8% across all 5 operating points; velocity field comparison shows < 5% NRMSE vs PIV data. Uncertainty bands from Monte Carlo UQ enclose experimental measurements at all points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/qoi-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Primary QOI is normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) directly mapped to clinical hemolysis acceptance criterion. Secondary QOIs (shear stress distribution, residence time) directly inform hemolysis model inputs. Clinical relevance confirmed by hematologist review documented in clinical-relevance memo CR-COU2-2024."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/validation-relevance-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments performed on identical FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry under VAD operating conditions (3000–5000 RPM, 3–7 L/min). Blood analog fluid (glycerol-water, matched viscosity) used with documented rheological characterization. Validation domain fully overlaps COU operating envelope."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/solver-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Iterative convergence verified: all residuals below 1e-6 for continuity and momentum; hemolysis scalar residual below 1e-8. Double-precision arithmetic used throughout. Round-off error estimated via perturbation analysis to be three orders of magnitude below discretization error. Documented in solver-error report SE-COU2-001."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/use-error-mrl5",
      "rationale": "Simulation setup independently reviewed by second qualified engineer per documented checklist (QC-SIM-COU2). Boundary condition assignment, turbulence model selection (SST k-omega), and hemolysis model parameters verified against published best-practice guidelines. No setup errors identified in independent review."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 5,
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/criteria/model-form-mrl5",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence model selected based on published FDA pump benchmark literature (Hariharan et al. 2011, Stewart et al. 2012). Power-law hemolysis model (Giersiepen-Wurzinger) validated against in-vitro data. Model form uncertainty quantified via comparison of three turbulence models; SST k-omega shows lowest systematic bias (< 3% hemolysis index error). Sobol sensitivity indices confirm model form is not dominant uncertainty source."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
